(TNI AU Aircrew Platform ? One-Page Summary) Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
(WHAT IT IS) Tj
0 -13 Td
(TNI AU Aircrew Platform is a frontend-only single-page application \(SPA\) for aircrew operations, built with React, TypeScript, TailwindCSS, and Vite.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(It centralizes operational readiness workflows in the browser without a backend API.) Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
(WHO IT'S FOR) Tj
0 -13 Td
(Primary persona: Indonesian Air Force \(TNI AU\) aircrew stakeholders such as Pilot, Flight Safety Officer, Ops Officer, Medical, and Commander/Admin roles.) Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
(WHAT IT DOES) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Shows a readiness dashboard and mission-profile-driven readiness score.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Manages E-Logbook entries and sortie-related operational records.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Supports ORM risk assessments and safety/incident reporting workflows.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Tracks training/currency status and schedule planning.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Handles NOTAM acknowledgment and operational awareness pages.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Enforces role-based route/action access for multiple operational roles.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Persists app data locally, including audit logs, and supports client-side CSV/PDF export.) Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
(HOW IT WORKS \(REPO-EVIDENCE ARCHITECTURE\)) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Client app: React SPA with BrowserRouter route-based pages \(core pages + dynamic feature modules\).) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? State layer: AppProvider uses React Context + useReducer as global state manager.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Data/persistence: initial mock data seeds state, then reads/writes full app state to browser localStorage.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Access control: RBAC utilities gate route visibility and write actions per role.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Derived analytics: readiness score is computed from state and exposed through context.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Delivery/runtime: Vite dev/build pipeline, static frontend deploy, and service-worker registration for basic offline behavior.) Tj
0 -13 Td
(? Integrations/back-end: Not found in repo \(no API client/service integration found\).) Tj
0 -13 Td
() Tj
0 -13 Td
(HOW TO RUN \(MINIMAL\)) Tj
0 -13 Td
(1. Install dependencies: `npm install`) Tj
0 -13 Td
(2. Start local dev server: `npm run dev`) Tj
0 -13 Td
(3. Build production assets \(optional\): `npm run build`) Tj
0 -13 Td
(4. Preview build locally \(optional\): `npm run preview`) Tj
